actory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:309:   operators/\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:328: Antes de chamar o supervisor, o workflow escreve um checkpoint de arranque, por exemplo:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:340: ### Bootstrap message contract do supervisor\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:342: Depois do bootstrap, o workflow deve activar o `sm_s3_visual_planning` com uma mensagem estruturada, n�o com um prompt improvisado.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:354:   \"operators_dir\": \".../b2_s3_visual_planning/operators\",\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:367: - o detalhe do comportamento individual de cada operator\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:368: - como o supervisor monitoriza os operators em execu��o\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:376: ## Operator architecture inside S3\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:380: ### Camada A - extraction / normalization operators\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:382: Esta camada cont�m os operators que fazem **an�lise sem�ntica delimitada** sobre o `s3_source_package.json` e produzem artefactos can�nicos no disco.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:384: A responsabilidade destes operators �:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:391: Estes operators **n�o devem** ser respons�veis por:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:395: - fazer dedupe global inter-operator\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:400: Esta camada pertence preferencialmente ao **supervisor + substrate**, n�o aos operators.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:404: - agrega��o dos outputs dos operators\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:410: Esta separa��o existe para evitar que os operators acumulem responsabilidades de pipeline e para manter a l�gica mec�nica centralizada numa camada mais control�vel.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:414: ## Taxonomy rica, operator layer est�vel\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:416: O S3 deve preservar uma **taxonomy rica de entidades visuais**. O sistema n�o deve ser empobrecido s� para reduzir o n�mero de operators.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:433: No entanto, esta riqueza sem�ntica **n�o implica** criar um operator diferente para cada microcategoria.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:435: A decis�o estrutural actual � preservar uma taxonomy ampla, mas oper�-la atrav�s de um conjunto menor de operators com fronteiras cognitivas est�veis.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:439: ## Mapa actual dos operators do S3\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:441: A operator layer actual do S3 passa a ser composta por 4 operators principais:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:489: Este mapa ainda ser� refinado operator por operator, mas a decomposi��o macro est� fechada nesta forma.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:497: A ideia n�o � usar o config da conta para decidir se um operator \"existe\" ou n�o, mas sim para modular:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:513: Isto significa que o comportamento do S3 deve ser **account-aware**, mas sem tornar a topologia de operators dependente de cada conta.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:519: A rela��o entre supervisor e operators n�o deve depender de prompts ad hoc.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:521: O S3 passa a assumir um modelo em que cada operator � invocado com:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:524: 2. um **operator-specific payload**\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:538: O operator-specific payload carrega o detalhe particular do contract de cada operator.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:540: O detalhe completo desta camada fica centralizado em `operators.md`.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:546: **Status:** base arquitectural do S3 actualizada ap�s fecho inicial da operator layer\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:550: - a separa��o Paperclip -> workflow -> supervisor -> operators\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:551: - a separa��o entre analysis operators e compile/merge logic\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:552: - a exist�ncia de 4 operators principais no S3\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:554: - a necessidade de um dispatch contract est�vel entre supervisor e operators\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:558: - contract exacto de cada operator\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:559: - output schema de cada operator\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\inputs.md:12: A ideia � que o supervisor do S3 normalize estes artefactos e gere um pacote-base �nico que possa ser entregue aos operadores do sector.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\inputs.md:113: Mais tarde, se necess�rio, o supervisor do S3 poder� derivar views especializadas para cada operador. Mas isso n�o faz parte desta primeira defini��o.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\inputs.md:119: O supervisor do S3 deve montar este input-base a partir de artefactos j� existentes no CFV3:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:1: # S3 - Operators\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:5: Este documento centraliza a defini��o da operator layer do S3 (Visual Planning).\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:9: - a l�gica geral da operator layer\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:10: - a separa��o entre analysis operators e compile/merge logic\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:12: - o mapa actual dos operators do S3\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:13: - o common dispatch contract do supervisor -> operator\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:14: - o papel do config por conta no comportamento dos operators\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:15: - a defini��o v1 consolidada dos 4 operators principais\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:17: Este documento ainda n�o fecha o contract final e imut�vel de cada operator individualmente. O objectivo desta vers�o � fixar uma v1 operacional suficientemente clara para implementa��o inicial e testes do S3.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:23: A operator layer do S3 segue a seguinte separa��o:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:25: ### Camada A - extraction / normalization operators\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:27: Os operators fazem:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:34: Os operators n�o devem ser respons�veis por:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:37: - merge inter-operator\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:46: - supervisor do S3\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:49: Esta separa��o existe para manter os operators semanticamente focados e evitar distribuir responsabilidade de pipeline por m�ltiplos agents.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:76: ## Rich taxonomy != operator explosion\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:80: > riqueza da taxonomy sem�ntica n�o implica explos�o do n�mero de operators.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:87: - e ainda assim a operator layer pode manter um n�mero controlado de operators est�veis\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:93: ## Mapa actual de operators do S3\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:95: A operator layer actual do S3 passa a ser composta por 4 operators principais.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:113: O config por conta � uma pe�a central do comportamento dos operators.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:115: A fun��o do config n�o � decidir se um operator existe ou n�o existe. A fun��o dele � modular o comportamento dos operators existentes.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:152: O desenho da operator layer deve permitir este grau de especializa��o por conta sem multiplicar operators � for�a.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:158: O supervisor deve invocar cada operator atrav�s de um contract padronizado.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:160: A ideia � evitar dispatch por prompt improvisado e garantir uma superf�cie est�vel entre supervisor e operator.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:165: 2. **operator-specific payload**\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:173: Este envelope carrega o contexto operacional comum necess�rio para qualquer operator do S3.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:191:   \"contract_version\": \"s3.operator_dispatch.v1\",\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:194:   \"supervisor_run_id\": \"sup_s3_001\",\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:195:   \"operator_run_id\": \"op_human_subject_001\",\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:196:   \"operator_name\": \"human_subject_extractor\",\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:228:     \"output_path\": \"runs/vid