law\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:315: ## Defini��o v1 dos 4 operators\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:347: #### `operator_payload` v1\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:408: #### `operator_payload` v1\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:472: #### `operator_payload` v1\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:532: - entidades j� bem cobertas pelos outros 3 operators\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:537: #### `operator_payload` v1\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:589: - compile posterior pelo supervisor/substrate\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:593: ## O que continua fora dos operators\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:595: Mesmo com estes 4 operators fechados em v1, continuam fora da sua responsabilidade:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:606: - os operators **identificam e estruturam**\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:607: - o supervisor/substrate **consolida**\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:615: - output schema formal de cada operator\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:616: - monitoriza��o p�s-dispatch pelo supervisor\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:625: **Status:** v2 da operator layer do S3\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:629: - a separa��o operators vs compile/merge logic\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:631: - o mapa actual de 4 operators principais\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:633: - o common dispatch contract v1 do supervisor -> operator\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:634: - a defini��o v1 operacional dos 4 operators\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:636: Pr�ximo passo natural: fechar a camada p�s-dispatch do supervisor e/ou formalizar o output schema base dos operators para implementa��o inicial.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\post_dispatch.md:5: Este documento descreve o que acontece no S3 depois que o supervisor despacha os operators.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\post_dispatch.md:9: - monitoriza��o da execu��o dos operators\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\post_dispatch.md:16: Este documento complementa `supervisor.md`, mas mant�m esta fase separada para evitar sobrecarga excessiva no documento do supervisor.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\post_dispatch.md:22: O S3 **n�o termina** quando os operators respondem ou quando parecem ter acabado.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\post_dispatch.md:26: 1. os outputs dos operators foram observados e validados\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\post_dispatch.md:35: ## Responsabilidade do supervisor nesta fase\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\post_dispatch.md:37: O supervisor continua a ser o dono do control plane do sector.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\post_dispatch.md:41: ### O que permanece no supervisor\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\post_dispatch.md:43: O supervisor deve continuar respons�vel por:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\post_dispatch.md:45: - decidir se um operator realmente concluiu com sucesso\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\post_dispatch.md:53: Certos trabalhos n�o devem depender apenas de julgamento conversacional do supervisor.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\post_dispatch.md:57: - leitura padronizada dos artefactos dos operators\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\post_dispatch.md:67: O supervisor continua dono da decis�o.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\post_dispatch.md:73: ## Fase 1 - Monitoriza��o dos operators\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\post_dispatch.md:75: Depois do dispatch, o supervisor entra numa fase de observa��o da execu��o.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\post_dispatch.md:77: ### O que deve monitorizar por operator\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\post_dispatch.md:79: Para cada operator activo, o supervisor deve observar:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\post_dispatch.md:90: Cada operator deve acabar mapeado num destes estados operacionais:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\post_dispatch.md:101: O supervisor deve monitorizar principalmente por artefactos persistidos no disco, n�o por respostas textuais soltas do agent.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\post_dispatch.md:105: ## Fase 2 - Valida��o dos outputs dos operators\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\post_dispatch.md:107: Quando um operator aparenta ter terminado, o supervisor valida o resultado.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\post_dispatch.md:109: ### Valida��o m�nima por operator\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\post_dispatch.md:114: 4. o conte�do � coerente com o `operator_name`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\post_dispatch.md:132: Se um operator falhar, o supervisor n�o deve, por defeito, reiniciar o sector inteiro.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\post_dispatch.md:136: O retry deve ser preferencialmente **selectivo por operator**.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\post_dispatch.md:140: - `human_subject_extractor` falha -> retry apenas deste operator\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\post_dispatch.md:141: - `object_artifact_extractor` produz schema inv�lido -> retry apenas deste operator\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\post_dispatch.md:151: ### Casos em que retry do operator pode n�o ser o caminho certo\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\post_dispatch.md:160: Nesses casos, o problema j� n�o � apenas do operator. Pode ser falha do supervisor, do bootstrap ou do sector.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\post_dispatch.md:165: - 1 retry selectivo por operator, quando a falha for recuper�vel\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\post_dispatch.md:166: - se falhar novamente, marcar operator como falhado\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\post_dispatch.md:167: - o supervisor decide ent�o se o sector fecha degradado ou falha completamente\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\post_dispatch.md:173: Quando os operators v�lidos terminam, o S3 entra na fase de compila��o.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\conte