ck2\\S3\\operators.md:93: ## Mapa actual de operators do S3\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:95: A operator layer actual do S3 passa a ser composta por 4 operators principais.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:113: O config por conta � uma pe�a central do comportamento dos operators.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:115: A fun��o do config n�o � decidir se um operator existe ou n�o existe. A fun��o dele � modular o comportamento dos operators existentes.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:152: O desenho da operator layer deve permitir este grau de especializa��o por conta sem multiplicar operators � for�a.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:158: O supervisor deve invocar cada operator atrav�s de um contract padronizado.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:160: A ideia � evitar dispatch por prompt improvisado e garantir uma superf�cie est�vel entre supervisor e operator.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:165: 2. **operator-specific payload**\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:173: Este envelope carrega o contexto operacional comum necess�rio para qualquer operator do S3.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:191:   \"contract_version\": \"s3.operator_dispatch.v1\",\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:194:   \"supervisor_run_id\": \"sup_s3_001\",\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\operators.md:195:   \"operator_run_id\": \"op_human_subject_001\",\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\