{"type":"message","id":"a441ba6e","parentId":"e7d51c03","timestamp":"2026-04-03T17:48:34.831Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Evaluating Git Status**\n\nI’m noticing that the `git status` command isn't showing me what I need because of untracked files in my workspace. That can be frustrating! I want to ensure my workspace reflects the right changes. I think a clearer overview would help me understand the situation better. So, maybe I should look for alternatives or more detailed commands to get my workspace sorted out! Let's keep it concise and efficient.","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_0f1f1c402b33ed570169cffd6836448191bfdfcc3d5ac61b98\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABpz_1rJL5e0p06zzMX_I_RJFi1Zr-yg0JtF9bj-en-p75moCcvku96xQDuSV7rThskGEIMv_0Ia-EjkNYFZCYRVdAB5pMPOpFVQCP2fjKOoZl4L09MmZZ9dDLCaywLncOeb3QEWdVWTn-1bZcaTzyCKto9uw-NmlgykSR2Y4ewwN-HQHUMsDuLO4H9yHLlHGQtowv1x8SZYR_lHRePighlSUw9USU2ln6h2vtqUYVmBerQ_1OwJw3deB8qugqAVh6FOzWmFmPPts6xUD8-DiiWSwazQkiI_u9weLHpeM-vSVNML73fQzYgdkZikxV_7MM7cTPbduPVDbpkt-LuC0zMy90_HNXSG2KNbX_ao1qH4QSvSxgd2ApL03QUJdRhIXpO4RsciYpYsqjSIwK6o6Blw6ASWDa5l_Nf8ztusqyVrSg8XC6W_7GU2BEIjqrGAVFwYES0aqlHe_uiPfD9kTF8Lgce1ff_drb76D9gxsdFh6Auznhbk9nI_Xu8F_Zb59_qPvzGYgpkdzWQbpH7FqMNYWJW-uzkkzoYwIGT8UVY3RlUop2IYsg2GlWdIfkiOG6whum0q4MH5BQpKDLLjaeAOvJQW0F_LL2YYNlTrdJ1j_RV5rAbt6Vodw0l4OeMnVXM5BqCqhCI9JqZY0GSfAHRGgIeuhTyba2nmJPyNWu2SqzDsdmsaVhhi9dmg8oJVJMpJTVR9KBIQ4rTkaX0hQqTHUwvQKP89Y0SIDtDbfBlDYW7J8uHm-kSATl4_ts2DQr4DPe_Voe1yJ4i8JQIO68ZEXY6nA_ZE5REf04vUiajgkaDUcSo8M9J-U8ghFwAOXm9iCNkuL4xTm09DHZdms5I0ICX9P8KMAhmgHHVdDRMXKgSvbepZxFiSEzS6cRmvoDkq3K1r7MggvhYZ1gn0IiYY7_NUA==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating Git Status**\\n\\nI’m noticing that the `git status` command isn't showing me what I need because of untracked files in my workspace. That can be frustrating! I want to ensure my workspace reflects the right changes. I think a clearer overview would help me understand the situation better. So, maybe I should look for alternatives or more detailed commands to get my workspace sorted out! Let's keep it concise and efficient.\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"Accomplished:\n- Proved the real supervisor->operator hop is possible in this environment without ACP.\n- The working primitive is:\n  - `exec -> openclaw agent --agent op_s3_human_subject_extractor --message \"...\" --json`\n- Ran the narrow end-to-end proof via:\n  - `content_factory_block2/helpers/real_run_s3_supervisor_one_operator_cli.py`\n- Result:\n  - real operator launch succeeded (`returncode: 0`)\n  - operator wrote real runtime artifacts and `output.json`\n  - supervisor compiled `compiled_entities.json`\n  - final sector status was `degraded_completed` only because just 1 operator was intentionally run, not because launch failed\n\nWhat changed:\n- Updated supervisor-facing docs/instructions to hard-pin the correct primitive and avoid ACP regression:\n  - `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_s3_visual_planning\\MISSION.md`\n  - `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_s3_visual_planning\\OPERATIONS.md`\n  - `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_s3_visual_planning\\CONTRACT.md`\n  - `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\supervisor.md`\n\nWhat was proven:\n- ACP/sessions_spawn was a false blocker for this hop.\n- The real operator can be launched now through the canonical CLI primitive.\n- Evidence:\n  - `runtime_realcheck/run_cli_probe/b2/sectors/s3_visual_planning/checkpoints/operator_cli_invoke_result.json`\n    - contains nested successful `openclaw agent --agent op_s3_human_subject_extractor ... --json` result\n  - `runtime_realcheck/run_cli_probe/b2/sectors/s3_visual_planning/operators/human_subject_extractor/output.json`\n    - real operator-produced output exists\n  - `.../status.json` and `.../checkpoint.json`\n    - both show completed\n  - `.../checkpoints/s3_final_checkpoint.json`\n    - `primitive: \"exec + openclaw agent --agent ... --json\"`\n\nImportant nuance:\n- The probe’s final sector status is still `degraded_completed`, but only because the validation intentionally ran one operator, then compiled with the others missing.\n- The supervisor->operator launch itself is no longer degraded.\n\nConclusion / whether Perseus can proceed:\n- Yes — Perseus can proceed.\n- The remaining issue was not a hard infra blocker; it was supervisor behavior/prompting drifting into ACP fallback.\n- If `sm_s3_visual_planning` now follows the updated docs and uses the CLI primitive, it should be able to launch at least one real operator for real.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0f1f1c402b33ed570169cffd6b5aa08191b74039c0f01dbef0\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":431,"output":590,"cacheRead":129152,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":130173,"cost":{"input":0.0010775000000000001,"output":0.00885,"cacheRead":0.032288,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.042215499999999996}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775238502338,"responseId":"resp_0f1f1c402b33ed570169cffd66b8a48191ac9e34cc89c2a415"}}
